dcterms:description: A large-scale dataset of gaze in free-viewing of videos, consisting of 1K videos with more than 600K frames and per-frame fixation annotations from 17 observers. The dataset includes diverse scenes, motion patterns, object categories, and activities.
dcterms:title: DHF1K (Dynamic Human Fixation)

dcterms:creator: S. Mathe
C. Sminchisescu
dcterms:description: The Hollywood-2 dataset comprises 1,707 videos from 69 Hollywood movies with 12 action categories. Human fixation data were tracked from 19 observers for free viewing and action recognition.
dcterms:title: Hollywood-2

dcterms:creator: S. Mathe
C. Sminchisescu
dcterms:description: The UCF sports fixation dataset contains 150 videos taken from the UCF sports action dataset, covering 9 common sports action classes. The fixation data were collected from viewers instructed to identify actions.
dcterms:title: UCF sports

dcterms:creator: H. Hadizadeh
M. J. Enriquez
I. V. Bajic
dcterms:description: The DIEM dataset is a public video eye-tracking dataset that includes 84 videos collected from publicly accessible video resources. It contains free-viewing fixations from around 50 observers.
dcterms:title: DIEM

dcterms:creator: CRCNS
dcterms:description: The CRCNS dataset is an eye-tracking database for a set of standard video sequences, providing fixation data for various video stimuli.
dcterms:title: CRCNS

dcterms:creator: T. Judd
F. Durand
A. Torralba
dcterms:description: MIT300 is a benchmark dataset of computational models of saliency to predict human fixations, providing a comprehensive evaluation of saliency models.
dcterms:title: MIT300

dcterms:creator: F. Yu
Y. Zhang
S. Song
A. Seff
J. Xiao
dcterms:description: LSUN is a large-scale image dataset constructed using deep learning with human involvement, aimed at various computer vision tasks.
dcterms:title: LSUN
